The United States has announced that it will provide over $308 million in humanitarian assistance for the people of Afghanistan. This brings the total U.S. humanitarian aid for Afghanistan and Afghan refugees in the region since October 2021 to nearly $782 million. The United States remains the largest donor of humanitarian aid in Afghanistan. Additionally, the United States will provide one million additional COVID-19 vaccine doses through COVAX, bringing the total to 4.3 million doses. The new assistance will be provided through independent humanitarian organizations and will address the growing humanitarian needs in Afghanistan, including healthcare shortages, drought, malnutrition, and the winter season. The United States is committed to supporting the Afghan people and is exploring all available options to help.